<div class="flow">
	<div class="two-column right-priority flow">
		<div class="flow">
			<h1>hello <span class="inline-block">there! o/</span></h1>
			<p>My name is Andy Chan, human being and stuff maker. This is my website, where I write about some of the stuff I make.</p>
			<p>You can find more about me on <a href="/about">the about page</a>.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="flow">
			<h2>links</h2>
			<div class="block-div">
				<p>You can find me in these places:</p>
				<a href="https://github.com/12beesinatrenchcoat" data-tooltip="GitHub. Code projects.">12beesinatrenchcoat</a>
				<a href="https://twitter.com/12bz_trenchcoat" data-tooltip="Twitter. Mostly anime art retweets.">@12bz_trenchcoat</a>
				<a href="https://www.youtube.com/c/AndyChanPineapples" data-tooltip="YouTube. Videos sometimes.">andy chan</a>
			</div>
			<div class="block-div">
				<p>and you can contact me at these places:</p>
				<a href="mailto:andy@12beesinatrenchco.at" data-tooltip="Email. Please no spam.">andy@12beesinatrenchco.at</a>
				<a href="javascript:void(0)" data-icon="discord" data-tooltip="Discord. Click to copy." onclick="navigator.clipboard.writeText('12beesinatrenchcoat#7664')">@12beesinatrenchcoat#7664</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="flow">
		<div>
			<h2>current project</h2>
			<p>I guess I'm working on something right now</p>
			<div>
				{% for item in collections.projects | reverse | limit(1) %}
					{% if item.data.status === "wip" or item.data.status === "on_hold" %}
						{% include "block.njk" %}
					{% endif %}
				{% endfor %}
			</div>
		</div>
		<div>
			<h2>latest blog posts</h2>
			<p>Sometimes I write things.</p>
			<div class="flow">
				{% for item in collections.posts | reverse | limit(3) %}
					{% include "block.njk" %}
				{% endfor %}
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>